# 1. Product Overview

## Product Name

BloomDraw

## One-Line Description

BloomDraw is an AI-powered drawing companion for kids that turns preloaded lessons, photos, and text prompts into traceable art, sketches, cartoons, and projector-ready drawing experiences.

## Product Type

Mobile and tablet app for iOS and Android.

## Long-Term Product Vision

BloomDraw will eventually pair with a physical drawing projector device. Children will select or create artwork in the app, then project it onto paper or a wall and trace/draw it.

## MVP Product Vision

The MVP focuses on building the app experience first. Hardware integration is not required in V1. Instead, the app should include a polished “Projector Preview Mode” that shows how an image would be prepared for projection.

---

# 2. Target Users

## Primary End Users

Children aged 3–12.

## Primary Buyers / Decision Makers

Parents, grandparents, relatives, and gift buyers.

## Secondary Future Users

Art and craft teachers, schools, after-school programs, learning centers, and hobby artists.

## Primary MVP Market Lens

D2C parent + child creative learning app.

B2B/school use is future positioning, not part of strict V1.

---

# 3. Core Problem

Children often want to draw but get discouraged because drawing from reference is difficult. They may struggle to turn what they see into a good-looking drawing. Parents want hands-on creative activities that are educational, screen-assisted, but not purely passive screen time.

BloomDraw solves this by helping children create, trace, and learn drawings through:

* preloaded step-by-step lessons
* image-to-line-art conversion
* image-to-sketch conversion
* image-to-cartoon conversion
* kid-safe AI prompt-to-image generation
* projector-ready preview modes

---

# 4. Core Value Proposition

BloomDraw makes drawing easier, more fun, more guided, and more confidence-building for kids.

It turns any idea, photo, or learning topic into traceable creative output.

---

# 5. MVP Goal

Build a beautiful, fast, polished iOS/Android app that demonstrates the complete BloomDraw app experience before hardware integration.

The MVP should prove:

1. Users can easily browse drawing content.
2. Kids and parents understand the drawing/tutorial experience.
3. The app feels modern, magical, premium, and child-friendly.
4. Uploaded/captured photos can become trace-ready styles.
5. AI prompt generation can create kid-safe drawing images.
6. AI-generated images can also produce simplified line-art versions.
7. The projector-preview concept is clear even without physical hardware.
8. The app is ready for investor demo, user pilot, and manufacturer conversations.

