# 6. MVP Scope

## Must-Have V1 Features

### A. Beautiful App Experience

Build a highly polished mobile/tablet app with:

* animated loader / splash experience
* modern home screen
* playful but premium UI
* smooth transitions
* animated cards
* bottom tab navigation
* mobile and tablet responsiveness
* friendly kid-safe visual language

The app should feel like a mix of:

* playful toy
* premium educational app
* magical creative studio
* parent-trustworthy learning product

### B. Home Screen

The home screen should show:

* hero section
* age filter
* featured drawing lessons
* content categories
* recent creations
* AI creation entry point
* camera/gallery upload entry point
* projector preview entry point
* favorites section if available

### C. Age Filter

Use age ranges instead of full child profiles in V1.

Required age filters:

* 3–5
* 6–8
* 9–12

The selected age range should influence visible/recommended content and difficulty.

Do not build full child profiles in V1.

### D. Preloaded Content Library

Create a structured content library with approximately 100 content items.

It is acceptable to use a mix of:

* polished sample/hero content
* placeholder content
* structured metadata
* simple generated/demo assets

The app should have visible categories even if some content items are placeholders.

Essential categories:

1. Alphabets
2. Numbers
3. Animals
4. Vehicles
5. Space
6. Nature
7. School/curriculum drawings
8. Cards/gifting templates

Optional additional categories if easy:

* shapes
* festivals
* landscapes
* people
* cute characters

### E. Preloaded Step-by-Step Drawing Tutorials

Preloaded drawings must support step-by-step tutorials.

Each drawing item should include:

* title
* category
* age range
* difficulty
* thumbnail
* final drawing
* projection-ready / tracing version
* 4–8 drawing steps
* favorite option
* projector preview button

Step count rules:

* easy drawings: 4 steps
* medium drawings: 6 steps
* harder drawings: 8 steps

### F. Camera/Gallery Upload

Users should be able to:

* open camera
* select from gallery
* crop/confirm image
* send image for transformation
* view generated output styles

Required output styles for uploaded/captured images:

1. Original preview
2. Line art
3. Pencil sketch
4. Coloring-page style
5. Cartoon style

True step-by-step tutorial generation is not required for uploaded images in V1.

If easy, include a “progressive tracing layers” fallback:

* outline
* major shapes
* details
* final trace version

But do not make this a blocker.

### G. AI Prompt-to-Image Generation

Users should be able to enter a prompt such as:

“cute elephant astronaut on the moon”

The app should generate:

1. Kid-safe image
2. Simplified line-art version
3. Projection-ready version

True step-by-step tutorial generation is not required for AI-generated images in V1.

If feasible, show progressive layers or a simple “AI drawing guide” as a bonus, but do not block the MVP on it.

### H. AI Safety Layer

The AI feature must include strong kid-safe controls.

Before generation:

1. Prompt is sent to moderation/safety function.
2. Unsafe prompts are blocked.
3. Borderline prompts can be safely rewritten.
4. Only kid-safe prompts go to image generation.
5. The final prompt sent to the image API should be optimized for child-friendly drawing output.

Required behavior:

* block violent, sexual, hateful, self-harm, adult, or unsafe content
* rewrite scary/aggressive prompts into gentle child-safe versions where appropriate
* return friendly kid-safe error messages
* never expose raw moderation details to the child

Example:

User prompt:
“dragon fighting monster with blood”

Safe rewrite:
“friendly dragon flying in a magical forest”

Or block if unsafe.

### I. Favorites and Recents

Since there is no login in V1, store favorites and recents locally on-device.

Required:

* favorite preloaded drawings
* view recent generated/uploaded creations
* remove favorite
* clear recents if easy

Optional:

* sync later after auth is added

### J. Projector Preview Mode

No real hardware connection is required in V1.

But build a polished Projector Preview Mode that shows how the selected image would be prepared for a projector.

Required controls:

* full-screen preview
* rotate
* zoom/resize
* adjust outline thickness if feasible
* brightness/high-contrast mode
* paper-size preview
* “Connect projector coming soon” state

This screen should make the future hardware product obvious.

### K. Backend Storage

Use Supabase.

Store anonymous data only.

Backend should store:

* anonymous session ID
* AI prompts
* safe rewritten prompts
* moderation result summary
* generated image metadata
* uploaded image metadata
* output style metadata
* timestamps
* selected age filter if relevant

Do not require user login in V1.

Do not build full accounts or cloud profile sync in V1.

### L. Real AI Integration Architecture

Build real API-ready integration through environment variables.

If API keys are not available, include a mock fallback so the app can still run locally.

The production path must be real and ready for keys.

Do not hardcode API keys in the app.

Do not put secret API keys in the Expo mobile app bundle.

AI calls should go through Supabase Edge Functions or a server-side layer.

